# Methodology

## Approach

The lab was designed to simulate a real-world attacker workflow:

1. Reconnaissance (Nmap scanning)
2. Enumeration (identifying active hosts)
3. Traffic Analysis (Wireshark)
4. Exploitation (WiFi handshake capture)
5. Post-Exploitation (password cracking)

## Key Learning Areas

* Understanding network protocols (ARP, ICMP)
* Observing how scanning tools generate traffic
* Identifying weaknesses in wireless security
* Applying offensive security techniques in a safe environment

## Future Improvements

* Add vulnerability scanning (Nessus/OpenVAS)
* Expand to Active Directory attack lab
* Implement defensive monitoring (SIEM tools)

